1. Fix the ViewModel to use a list, not comma-separated strings

Add this to your RebuiltPartsViewModel:

public List<int> BusIdsList =>
    string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(BusId)
        ? new List<int>()
        : BusId.Split(',')
               .Select(int.Parse)
               .ToList();


Your DB query can remain the same (still returns comma-separated values).
This property simply transforms "7,8,9,10,11" → [7,8,9,10,11].

✅ 2. In your popup editor MultiSelect, bind the Value properly

In _RbPopUpEditor.cshtml:

@(Html.Kendo().MultiSelect()
    .Name("BusId")  // MUST MATCH viewmodel property name
    .DataTextField("BusName")
    .DataValueField("BusId")
    .Placeholder("Select Vehicle..")
    .Filter("contains")
    .AutoBind(true)
    .Value(Model.BusIdsList)   // <--- PREPOPULATE!
    .DataSource(ds =>
    {
        ds.Read(r => r.Action("ReadBuses", "RebuiltParts"));
    })
)
